<p>The mistake most teams make is reporting these metrics in isolation. A blog post with 10,000 pageviews and zero conversions has a different story than one with 500 pageviews and 25 leads.</p>
<p>Always pair traffic metrics with conversion data. That connection is what separates vanity reporting from ROI measurement.</p>
<p>Your <a href="/blog/organic-ctr-by-position/">organic click-through rates</a> directly impact how much traffic each ranking position delivers. Position 1 gets roughly 10x the clicks of position 10.</p>
